* ============================================================
* LMDB_ROUTING_GAP_REPRO.DTS
* Purpose: Prove/record the current routing gap:
*   - SETLMDB sets orderstate to <cdx> + <tag>
*   - LIST/TOP/SMARTLIST still route through legacy CDX open
*     and emit: "Failed to open index: ... (unable to read index)"
*
* Keep ASCII only.
* ============================================================

SET ECHO OFF
ECHO ===== LMDB ROUTING GAP REPRO START =====

* --- Clean slate
SCHEMAS CLOSE
SELECT 0

* --- Open target table
USE STUDENTS
AREA

* --- Ensure physical first
SETLMDB 0
ECHO --- Baseline LIST in physical order (should NOT try CDX) ---
LIST 3

* --- Activate LMDB order (this sets orderstate to .cdx + TAG)
ECHO --- Activate SETLMDB (expect: state prints OK) ---
SETLMDB students LNAME
SETLMDB

* --- Now trigger the gap on purpose:
*     Any command that consults orderstate and tries to open CDX will emit the error.
ECHO --- Trigger legacy CDX open via TOP ---
TOP

ECHO --- Trigger legacy CDX open via LIST ---
LIST 5

ECHO --- Trigger legacy CDX open via SMARTLIST (if implemented) ---
SMARTLIST 5

* --- Flip tag and repeat (shows gap is independent of chosen tag)
ECHO --- Switch tag to SID and trigger again ---
SETLMDB students SID
SETLMDB
TOP
LIST 5
SMARTLIST 5

* --- Clean exit
ECHO ===== LMDB ROUTING GAP REPRO END =====